核心能力 Competence
■ 職能治療專業知識與理論
具備職能治療專業知識理論基礎，以為專業技能奠基。 Professional Knowledge and Theories of Occupational Therapy
Acuire Professional Knowledge and Theories of Occupational Therapy in order to Develop Therapeutic Skills■ 職能治療專業技能
具備職能治療專業技能，以提供個案職能表現之評估、分析與治療的能力。 Occupational Therapy Therapeutic Skills
Acuire Occupational Therapy Therapeutic Skills to Provide Evaluation, Analysis and Intervention for Clients' Occupational Performance■ 溝通表達及團隊合作之能力
培養適切溝通表達及團隊合作能力，以建立良好的醫病關係及專業團隊互動。 Communication and Interdisciplinary Cooperation Abilities
Acuire Communication Proficiency and Interdisciplinary Cooperation Abilities in order to Establish Therapeutic Relationship and Improve Professional Team Interacttion■ 獨立思考及問題解決之能力
培養具有獨立思考、臨床推理及問題解決的能力，並能終身學習。 Indipendent Critical Thinking and Problem Solving Abilities
Cultivate Indipendent Critical Thinking, Clinical Reasoning and Problem Solving Abilities, and Develop Lifelong Learning□ 創新與領導能力
培養具有創新與領導的能力，以為專業技能或研究奠基。 Innovative and Leadership Abilities
Cultivate Innovative and Leadership Abilities in order to Develop Therapeutic Skills and Professional Research 

課程概述 Course Description
       This course contains 1 lecturer and 2 practice credits. Practice is emphasized to facilitate experiential learning about professional issues. It reviews some professional basics and introduces some advanced practice guidelines to prepare the occupational therapy students for fieldwork practice. Through the semester, the crafts, modalidities, and techniques are introduced with practice experience. The issues of therapentic relationship, clinical reasoning, activity analysis and application are addressed to build up the professional identity. Evidence-based practice are emphasized through hand-on experience of scientific literature review and in-class discussionThis course contains 1 lecturer and 2 practice credits. Practice is emphasized to facilitate experiential learning about professional issues. It reviews some professional basics and introduces some advanced practice guidelines to prepare the occupational therapy students for fieldwork practice. Through the semester, the crafts, modalidities, and techniques are introduced with practice experience. The issues of therapentic relationship, clinical reasoning, activity analysis and application are addressed to build up the professional identity. Evidence-based practice are emphasized through hand-on experience of scientific literature review and in-class discussion    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    1.學習生理疾病患者之運動、知覺和認知功能的評估方法
2.瞭解生理疾病患者之動作控制訓練的理論基礎與臨床技巧
3.瞭解兒童之動作、視知覺、認知和社會心理功能的發展
4.學習兒童之動作、視知覺、認知和社會心理功能的評估方法    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Orientation, Evaluation of motor system2Evaluation of perception and cognition (I)3Evaluation of perception and cognition (II)4Brunnstrom approach5Rood approach / Sensory processing and modalities6Development of postural control 7Visual perceptual development8Play 9Mid-term Exam 10Bobath (NDT) approach 11PNF approach (I) 12Feeding and oral motor skills  13Development of fine motor  14Development of fine motor / Motor relearning program15Development of cognitive function / Contemporary task-oriented approach 16Development of cognitive function / Novel strategies in stroke rehabilitation17Psychosocial and emotional domains18Final Exam & Course Evaluation 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


